<br>
I skipped 7 pages of responses so let me just make two points that I think are very important.  <br>
<br>
1.  There is nothing wrong with sharing frustration, whether it is in a calm rational form or an explosion.  You have to release what is bothering you and frankly, posting it is far better than nuking someone in game...<br>
<br>
2.  Those that criticize this rant...All I can say is that with 15+ years in sales (what customer service really is, even though the corporate shiteaters want it called something more people friendly, and follow up service is simply retention and renewal of sales) and even more time working as a volunteer in scouting, local sports associations, and other organizations that use volunteerism and their means of creating slave labor, I have seen and taken a lot of abuse by assholes who forget that I am a volunteer.  I do my best to conduct myself in a fair and professional manner.  There were times that I wanted to tell someone off, but I always grinned and did my duty.  When I was no longer representing whatever organization (even though people knew I did volunteer for those organizations) I spoke freely and quite vehemently at times.<br>
<br>
My point?  Shut the hell up.  When Tweety, in this case, is here on this board, releasing some frustration about the assholes and yes we have many, many, many, in this game, he or she (sorry can't remember which) is not representing Verant in any manner.  if that is the case then everyone who is or has been a guide better never post again.  Most folks that I know that have been guides have been soured by the experience.  Volunteer work is meant to be gratifying, a means to give something back to the community from whence we took enjoyment or friendship, not as a way for an individual to be repeatedly kicked in the groin and asked if it hurt.<br>
<br>
I feel truly bad that tweety has gone through the BS that nearly every volunteer faces.  What makes it worse, is the anonymity of the game and the fact that people who obviously lack the social skills to have many friends or any semblence of a real life think that their opinion means shit in to anyone anywhere.  Frankly, if one wants quality from a volunteer, one must first show quality...I have always, and I mean always, strive to be as courteous as possible to volunteers (in this case guides) because I know the kind of crap they have to deal with.<br>
<br>
A piece of wisdom: Speak your mind, but be sure to have a mind to speak with. <p>Syke Auttic 51 monk (Stone Guard)<br>
Sssyke Auttic 23 monk (Shadow Killers)<br>
http://www.cageofrage.com
